reviewText:
Being a big Tom & Jerry fan, I actually already had all the cartoons in the set from various other DVD's.  I do like that WB mixes the classic-era T & J shorts (including a couple from the oft-overlooked Chuck Jones period) with the new.  The Tom & Jerry Tales episode "The Cat Nebula" is certainly one of the strangest cartoons in the duo's long history. . .and it's all the more entertaining for it.

At just under an hour, this is nice way to get your fix of space-themed cartoons featuring everyone's favorite cat and mouse team.  But with so much of their output readily available already, true fans will probably want to seek out the complete collections.
not bad. not many episodes but better than nothing.
My nephew loved this! He has other Tom & Jerry DVD's, but really got a kick out of this one! Highly recommended!
Works perfectly, got them on time. Wrap in plastic, all good
